  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Resilience and Livelihood Through Climate Sensitive Agriculture</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in ten (10) communities in two (2) Chiefdoms: Kissi Teng Chiefdom (Koindu, Kangama, Guadu, Tangabu and Bayama Lela) and Kissi Kama Chiefdom (Dea, Pelewahun, Kunduma, Kondorma and Korkorma) to contribute to CAFOD&#x2019;s Food and livelihood security and Emergency preparedness, response and recovery programme framework. Caritas Kenema will implement this project in collaboration with appropriate line ministries (MAFFS, MSW and MOHS) and local councils/Stakeholders. The project is targeting vulnerable groups (women and youths) and exceptional cases of men headed vulnerable households in rural communities. The project is also designed to increase local ownership, involvement, monitoring and accountability systems towards sustainability. 

This project will contribute and complement the Kailahun District council development plan to ensure the availability of adequate food, access to income and malnutrition prevention and control by 2023.</narrative>
  </description>
